bug.short_desc: Problem with Opacity and Scrollbars in Chrome 4

long_desc.thetext: Created attachment 719 Scrollbar has strange colors
I checked it on my mac and it's not happening on the mac. --> to Jonny
Confirmed on Chrome 4.0.x on Windows XP.
This bug is already reported at Chronium: http://code.google.com/p/chromium/issues/detail?id=24524
I will update this issue when the chronium guys fix the brower bug.
There is a workaround for this problem: Turning qx.nativeScrollBars off only for chrome! There should be a possiblity to do that.

> There is a workaround for this problem: Turning qx.nativeScrollBars off only > for chrome! There should be a possiblity to do that. Yes, this is a possibility to work around the issue. A possibility which an application should choose to implement. We would definetely overshoot the target here if we would change this in the framework, since this bug is application-specific. Plus: we would force all other users to adapt this setting even if they're not affected.
Closed all bugs already shipped with a release.
